  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 8 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 2 critical, 9 high, 12 medium, 16 normal. Key bases needing attention include Chişinău (RMO/LUKK), Iaşi (IAS/LRIA) and Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP); plus 8 other bases. 12 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS) and Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV). Network hotspots: Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Porto Santo (PXO/LPPS) and 3 others. Primary drivers: mist, low cloud base and RVR limitations. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Turku (TKU/EFTU), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS) and 9 others.",
